On February 14, 2012, the President signed two bills into law. The first bill, H.R. 588, renamed the Noxubee National Wildlife Refuge in Mississippi to the Sam D. Hamilton Noxubee National Wildlife Refuge. The second bill, H.R. 658, known as the "FAA Modernization and Reform Act of 2012," allocated budget resources for the Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) until FY 2015. It also encouraged the acceleration of the Next Generation Air Transportation System and air traffic control modernization.